        <span class="wowHead" id="challenge"><h2>The Context and Challenge</h2></span>

          <p class="challengeText"><b class="redText">The Project</b><br>
          Over the course of four weeks at Epicodus, level three students in Design class were to choose an indepedent project to work on. The project could be anything from redesigning a website or creating our own with a specific topic.<br><br>
          <b class="redText">The Choice</b><br>
          I originally chose a different project idea and spent a week guiding my efforts towards that subject but ultimately scrapped it. I decided to go with one of my most frequently used websites: Wowhead.<br><br>
          <b class="redText">The Challenge</b><br>
          Undertaking such a huge database website was initially overwhelming. I had so much content to work with and little time. I found patterns of where information was being thrown and was able to creatively condense it and present it in an updated modern look.<br>
          <img class="screen" src="../assets/img/ScreenTop.png">
          <br><br>
          <b class="redText">Modern. Sleek. Clean.</b><br>
          Having so little time in order to work with a database that has been accumulating information for over ten years was a challenge, but I dove in head first. My design keywords are modern, sleek, and clean. Wowhead's website could be described as cluttered, loud, and overwhelming. The challenge of transforming it into my ideal website was one that needed lots of brainstorming and inspiration.
          </p>
      </div>
